correctness.rationale: Several key fields do not align with the article and/or are internally inconsistent with the schema’s intent. Major issues: (1) ALD method and plasma use: TeO2 is marked as PEALD with plasmaPower=200 W, but the article describes thermal ALD (no plasma) for TeO2 at 80 °C (Sec. 3.1, Fig. 3.5–3.7). Te is also thermal ALD with MeOH codosing (Sec. 2.3). plasmaPower should be omitted and TeO2 method set to TALD. (2) Pressure: a single 500 mTorr is given, but Te deposition uses 500 mTorr during Ar purge and 5000 mTorr during Te deposition (Sec. 2.2–2.3). The Te step pressure is incorrect/missing. (3) Dosing and purge times for Te: extraction uses 1000 ms/200 ms and 200 ms purges; the article specifies three MeOH pulses of 500 ms overlapped with BTMS-Te (2 s), followed by three Te(OEt)4 pulses (2 s), with 10 s Ar purges (Sec. 2.3). (4) SupercycleDesign: a TeO2–Te supercycle is not reported for the TeO2/Te heterostructure; they deposit TeO2 then Te sequentially. Supercycles are used for TeOx (BTMS-Te and TeO2 with H2O) with m:n ratios (Sec. 3.3, Fig. 3.24), not for TeO2/Te. Current supercycle entry is misleading. (5) Thickness control inconsistency: GPC values (TeO2 ≈ 0.6 Å/cycle) are correct, but numberofCycles=40 with filmThickness=15 nm is inconsistent; 15 nm TeO2 would require ~2500 cycles (Sec. 3.1, Fig. 3.7–3.9). (6) MaterialProperties lack traceability or contradict the article: refractiveIndex=2.4 and bandGap=3.5 eV via Tauc plot were not measured/reported (3.5 eV appears as calculated value in refs., Sec. 1.3, Fig. 1.6–1.7). Electrical resistivity=0.001 Ω·m, carrier density=1e18 m⁻³, mobility=10 cm²/V·s by Hall are not reported for ALD TeO2 or Te films; TeO2 is treated as a high-k dielectric with leakage metrics, not semiconductor transport (Sec. 3.1, Fig. 3.9–3.10). Uniformity=5% and conformality AR=10 are not provided. Film density 5.2 (unit GM-PER-DeciM3) is wrong and not reported; as-grown TeO2 density is not given. (7) Chemical composition inconsistency: materialDeposited is “TeO2 and Te,” but chemicalComposition and composition fields describe TeO2 only (Te:O=1:2), conflicting with a heterostructure. (8) DeviceProperties: on/off=1e6 occurs at cryogenic temperatures (10 K) for TeO2/Te or TeOx devices (Sec. 3.17(d), 3.24(e)); thresholdVoltage=0.3 V and SS=60 mV/dec are not clearly supported for the TeO2/Te devices at RT; device structure varies in the article. Corrections needed: set TeO2 method to TALD and remove plasmaPower; provide dual pressures for Te steps; correct Te dosing/purge times; remove or replace supercycle with the TeOx supercycle if that is the intended process; reconcile GPC, cycles, and thickness; restrict material/device properties to values actually reported (e.g., dielectric constant k≈12.4, leakage, breakdown; TeO2 amorphous; TeO2/Te FET RT on/off ~10^3, cryo ~10^8); and split into two processes (TeO2 ALD and Te ALD) or clearly represent TeOx supercycle if applicable.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and factually inconsistent with the article and the schema. Key issues: (1) Multiple ALD processes described in the article are collapsed into a single process. Missing separate, coherent processes for: ALD TeO2 (Te(OEt)4 + H2O, 80 °C, 500 mTorr), ALD Te with MeOH co-dosing (BTMS-Te + MeOH + Te(OEt)4, specific pulse sequence and 5000 mTorr during Te deposition), ALD TeOx supercycle (m:n design; optimal 2:3), and the ALD IGZO supercycle (225 °C, In/Zn/Ga cycles). (2) Method mislabeling: TeO2 is incorrectly set as PEALD with 200 W plasma; the article reports thermal ALD (no plasma) for TeO2 and Te. PlasmaPower should be removed/corrected. (3) Process parameters incorrect/incomplete: pressure should reflect 500 mTorr during purge and 5000 mTorr during Te growth; dosing/purge times for Te must capture the reported sequence (MeOH 500 ms pulses ×3 overlapped with 2 s BTMS-Te, 10 s Ar purges; Te(OEt)4 2 s ×3 with 10 s purges). Current 200 ms purge and 1000 ms dosing are not traceable. (4) Thickness control inconsistency: numberofCycles = 40 with GPC (0.6 Å/cycle for TeO2, 1.0 Å/cycle for Te) does not match the reported film thicknesses (e.g., 15 nm TeO2 capacitors require ~250 cycles; TeO2 seeding 5–50 cycles; Te typically 80 cycles). (5) SupercycleDesign is inappropriately used for the TeO2/Te stack but the TeOx supercycle (m:n) that is actually reported is missing. (6) Material properties are largely fabricated: refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap measurement (Tauc), resistivity, mobility, uniformity (5%), conformality (AR=10), roughness (0.5 nm), and film density (5.2 g/dm3) are not reported in the article and/or have wrong units. The article reports dielectric properties for TeO2 (k=12.4; leakage <1e-7 A/cm² at 0.5 MV/cm; breakdown 1.6–3.8 MV/cm) and specific roughness values (TeO2 ~0.15 nm at 3 nm; TeO2/Te ~1.1 nm), which are not captured. (7) Device properties are not aligned: extracted μFE=10 cm²/V·s, SS=60 mV/dec, Vth=0.3 V, ION/IOFF=1e6 do not match TeO2/Te FET data (ION/IOFF ~1e3 at RT, >1e8 at low T; μFE ~2.5 cm²/V·s wafer-average; Rc ~18.8 Ω·mm) nor IGZO device metrics (ION/IOFF ~1e10). (8) Several fields lack traceability (reactor manufacturer “In-house”, conformality, refractive index, band gap method), and combining “TeO2 and Te” under one materialDeposited leads to semantic incoherence. To improve: add distinct process instances for ALD TeO2, ALD Te (with MeOH sequence), ALD TeOx supercycle (include m:n counts and subcycleSequence), and ALD IGZO; correct ALD method to TALD and remove plasmaPower; fix pressure and dosing/purge times per reported sequences; align cycles and thickness with GPC; replace material properties with the reported dielectric/leakage/breakdown and measured roughness; supply device metrics tied to the correct material and temperature; only include uniformity/conformality values that are traceable (e.g., wafer mapping for Raman/thickness if given).
